# Theme Consistency Rules

## Theme System
All UI elements must support both light and dark themes using the CSS custom properties defined in [resources/css/app.css](mdc:resources/css/app.css).

### Required Theme Classes
- Always use semantic color classes: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`
- Use theme-aware colors: `bg-card`, `text-muted-foreground`, `bg-accent`
- Never use hardcoded colors like `bg-white`, `text-black`, `bg-gray-100`

### Theme Toggle Implementation
- All pages must include theme toggle functionality
- Use `data-theme-toggle` attribute for theme toggle buttons
- Theme preference is stored per user in database via [app/Models/User.php](mdc:app/Models/User.php)

### CSS Variables Usage
```css
/* Use these semantic color variables */
--background: Light/Dark background
--foreground: Light/Dark text
--card: Card backgrounds
--border: Border colors
--primary: Primary brand color
--muted: Muted text/backgrounds
--accent: Accent colors
```

### Theme Transition
- All elements must have smooth transitions: `transition: background-color 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease, border-color 0.3s ease`
- Use the `.dark` class on `<html>` element for dark mode
- Theme switching is handled by [resources/js/app.tsx](mdc:resources/js/app.tsx)

### Examples
```html
<!-- ✅ Correct -->
<div class="bg-card text-foreground border-border">
<button class="bg-primary text-primary-foreground hover:bg-primary/90">

<!-- ❌ Wrong -->
<div class="bg-white text-black border-gray-200">
<button class="bg-blue-500 text-white hover:bg-blue-600">
```